’Ů@84d81860909fa7d608c821f91e6a29d9a5e46ec96e8195c02393e89a02b33934ÚTitle: title: mv
Path: Examples
Content:
Rename a file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mv before.txt after.txt


```
Move a file into a directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mv test.txt my/subdirectory


```
Move only if source file is newer than target file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mv -u new/test.txt old/


```
Move many files into a directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mv *.txt my/subdirectory


```
Move a file into the "my" directory two levels up in the directory tree.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mv test.txt .../my/


```
